# Normalize line endings to LF on checkout everywhere. GitHub's Windows CI
# runners default to core.autocrlf=true, which converts text files to CRLF on
# checkout — and Biome's formatter (lineEnding=lf) then flags every file as
# "needs formatting", failing CI. Forcing eol=lf here overrides autocrlf so the
# runner, local dev, and contributors all get the same LF the repo stores.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets — never apply EOL conversion (text=auto usually detects these,
# but be explicit so a heuristic miss can't corrupt them).
*.png   binary
*.ico   binary
*.icns  binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.dll   binary
*.exe   binary
*.wav   binary
*.onnx  binary
*.bin   binary
*.gguf  binary
